ANTHRAX, HUMAN - RUSSIA (WESTERN SIBERIA) (02)
******************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
See Also
Anthrax, human - Russia (Western Siberia) 990816201918
Anthrax, human - Russia (Buryatia) 990713221800
Anthrax, human - Russia (Buryatia) (04) 990719221904
Date: Mon, 16 Aug 1999 10:58:26 -0400
From: "Marjorie P. Pollack" <pollackmp@mindspring.com>
Source: Itar-Tass 16 Aug, 1999 [edited

Four people who contracted anthrax were hospitalized in the Novosibirsk
region.
[The Novosibirsk regions is in the southern portion of Western Siberia,
sharing a border with kazahkstan. All of them are residents of
Nizhnecheremoshnoye village of Krasnoozersk district of the Novosibirsk
region where an outbreak of this dangerous infectious disease has been
registered. A quarantine was imposed on Nizhnecheremoshnoye village, and
there are armed guards on all the roads from the village.
It was established that all the hospitalized people were cutting carcasses
of slaughtered animals, Vladimir Mikheyev, chief state sanitary physician
for the region, told a news conference on Monday. It was established that
more than 20 cows had anthrax. Before it became known that the animals were
ill, their meat was sold to neighboring villages and more than 500 kilograms
of meat was kept in the same warehouse with the carcasses of slaughtered
animals was delivered to canteens of two bread-baking plants in Novosibirsk.
The last incidenT of anthrax in the Novosibirsk region was registered 15
years ago. One person then contracted anthrax.
